Address: Lot 17 Bella Rosa Estate Werribee VIC 3030
Description:
The Wait is Over... Nest or Invest...
Ray White Truganina Proudly presents this great opportunity to build your dream home, on this beautiful block of land in the highly sought after Bella Rosa Estate in Werribee.
Stage 3 Now Selling
Imagine establishing a new life for you and your family in an established community that is bordered by established streets and all the amenities that come with it. This can all be yours at Bella Rosa Werribee.
Centrally located close to all things convenient, Bella Rosa offers precious exclusivity that can only come from being a brand new community neighbouring the admired St. Andrew's Estate, an established residential locality. The perfect mix of location and land upon which to create the ultimate lifestyle has been selected - all you need to do is hand pick the position that suits you.
Only 30 minute drive to the Melbourne CBD, Bella Rosa is a unique residential opportunity with leafy surrounds, striking streetscapes and an exciting array of extraordinary living choices. Residents will enjoy easy train, bus and road access to all major Melbourne destinations, and when travelling by air, will have the choice of Melbourne and Avalon Airports located within 30 minute drive from the estate.
Closer to home it is a short drive to local shopping centres such as Werribee Plaza where you can satisfy all your shopping requirements. A range of primary and secondary schools and higher education facilities are also close by, including the highly sought after St. Andrews Primary School and the Victoria University Werribee Campus.
Vast open spaces are close at hand including Gordon O'Keife Reserve and the Werribee Racecourse. Werribee Park, home to Werribee Park Mansion, Victoria's Open Range Zoo, the State Rose Garden and the State Equestrian Centre and Hotel is another must see attraction that is right at your doorstep.
For those who love the water, Werribee South beach is just minutes away and is perfect for swimming, fishing, boating, and strolling - or for just building sandcastles with the kids. Life gets even easier with a range of excellent schools, shops, eateries, transport and recreational facilities all at your doorstep, meaning you will be well positioned to enjoy the best that Werribee has to offer.
Saturday mornings can be spent playing a game of golf at the Werribee Park Golf Club, or enjoying getting back to nature at Werribee Park which contains Werribee Park Mansion, Victoria's Open Range Zoo and the State Rose Garden. The possibilities are truly limitless.
Please call Yash on 0410 840 500 or Mark on 0425 400 600 to find out more!

Description:
Under Contract Harcourts
Impressively scaled and contemporary in design, this beautifully designed family home was built for those who love to entertain! Spread over 2 luxurious levels, the property is highlighted by features such as a stunning chef's kitchen, enormous alfresco area and grand master ensuite. Sitting on over 630sqm (approx.) of land and positioned opposite Bothwell Green Reserve you'll be sure to be impressed.
The family will be spoilt for choice with a total of 6 indoor and outdoor living areas to choose from. Showcasing a front formal living and dining area perfect for formal occasions, huge rumpus room positioned at the rear of the home and an upstairs kids retreat. The family domain sits at the heart of the home and incorporates an informal open plan living and dining area as well as a stunning kitchen designed to impress with large island bench, stone benchtops, 2 separate sinks and servery. Indoor living extends outdoors with seamless access out to the oversized alfresco area, a truly remarkable space to host large gathering or entertain family and friends.
The palatial master bedroom is accompanied by a large Walk-in robe and stunning ensuite featuring dual vanity, oversized shower, and spa bath perfect to wind down in at the end of a long day. The master bedroom also offers the bonus of a balcony with views out to Bothwell Green Reserve. Three remaining bedrooms are fitted with built in robes, serviced by a sparkling central bathroom.
Additional features include ducted heating, evaporative cooling, ducted vacuum system and internal access from the double remote garage! Inspect now to avoid disappointment

Description:
North facing titled land ready to build in Ellarook! Truganina's best estate!
The Phone Code for this property is: 38592. Please quote this number when phoning or texting.
This north facing 392m² lot is in the prime position in Ellarook Estate in Stage 2 (Lot 218), close to the main entrance and walking distance to the proposed train station and future primary school.
With 14m frontage and 28m depth, will allow you numerous options for single storey and double storey house designs. With this titled block,you can build right away and get the $25K new home builder grant and $10K for eligible first home builders.
This perfectly sized block is located just around the corner from the Central Community Park and the future on-site primary school.
10 minute drive to Tarneit Train Station and Shopping Centre.
25 minutes to the City- 5 minutes to the Freeway
Connecting to a healthy outdoor lifestyle is easy at Ellarook with over 8ha of green space and reserves, including a central park and playground, designed to enrich the whole community. Further afield you'll find Ellarook connected by playgrounds, parks, wetlands, walking and bike paths, including the Federation Bike Trail. At Ellarook, you and your family will be inspired to live. Ellarook is being developed by Intrapac who have some amazing estates across Melbourne including the award winning Somerfield estate in Keysborough.
Location: Ellarook is surrounded by all the things that make a wonderful life. Be spoilt for choice with three major shopping centres nearby, any number of local restaurants and cafes and 10 medical centres in the area. Close to schools, shopping and surrounded by Werribee Park, Werribee Mansion, Werribee Open Range Zoo, and within easy access to the Surf Coast and Bellarine Peninsula, Ellarook truly has it all.

Set on a grand allotment of approximately 649Sqm of land, lounge with ducted heating system, split cooling system, freshly painted walls, brand new German engineered floor board, brand new tiles in the kitchen, massive Alfresco with adjoining pergola and two car garage. The generously-sized backyard has a low maintenance vibe with plenty of room to create an outdoor living area and more. Close to all local amenities and minutes to drive shopping centre, child-care, schools and easy access to Hoppers crossing train station and Princess Freeway.
Features of this beautiful property includes:
3 bedrooms with BIR's
Renovated kitchen with brand new tiles
Split cooling system
Ducted heating system
Brand new German engineered floor board and down lights
Low maintenance front yard and backyard garden

Description:
TITLED LAND Lot 2285 - Gawler Street (Riverwalk)
Build your dream home sooner on this titled lot at Riverwalk.
Fresh thinking and thoughtful design are at the forefront of the Riverwalk. Here, you can choose a new way of life on the banks of the Werribee River. Contemporary architecture nestles into natural surrounds and amenities are easily accessible.
Within Riverwalk itself, the planned town centre will feature a variety of shops and cafes. With direct access to the Princes Freeway and moments from public transport, you'll get where you need to easily. Youll also enjoy being close to the Werribee Town Centre, shops, schools, public transport and more.

Description:
Lot 2748 Eskdale Street PREMIUM - THE PROMENADE Collection 3
Create an enviable lifestyle at The Promenade, the gateway to the exceptional Riverwalk Premium within the established Riverwalk community in dynamic Werribee. Surround yourself with natural beauty in this exclusive parkside setting where more than 100,000 sqm of lush Riverfront parkland is just five minutes walk away.
The Promenades impressive entry features a wide tree-lined boulevard delivering a unique opportunity to nestle your dream home amongst mature trees and street landscaping. Enjoy an active lifestyle with the utmost convenience with Lollipop Creek and the Village Park within easy walking distance. A shared path will connect you to the Federation Trail that meanders beside the Werribee River for a scenic journey into the heart of Werribee. Take advantage of regular bus services to the suburbs flourishing amenity from a bus stop right on your doorstep. A premium parkside lifestyle by the river awaits at The Promenade.
A project by Development Victoria. Visit myriverwalk.com.au

Description:
Titled land & build your dream home
This fantastic opportunity to secure this approximately 392m2 titled land and ready build your dream home in Saltwater Coast Estate. Saltwater parklands have been architecturally landscaped and are comprised of BBQs, boardwalks, shelters, fitness stations, and play equipment. Saltwater Lifestyle Centre with fully equipped gym, indoor and outdoor pool, tennis courts, function room, café and BBQ facilities. Public transport is also at your doorstep with a frequent bus route direct to Williams Landing Station via Sanctuary Lakes Shopping Centre.
Perfectly positioned to make the most of the lifestyle opportunities:
Tribeca shopping village including supermarket, shops, childcare, swim school and leisure centre
Access to Saltwater Coast Life Style Centre
Educational facilities just a few minutes away (Saltwater P-9 College, St Mary of the Cross Catholic Primary School and Point Cook South College)
Saltwater Sporting Reserve, Parklands, protected wetlands

Description:
SOLD OFF MARKET!
Built by Profile Homes, this home is enviably located in a quiet cul-de-sac with security gate entrance and golf course at the end of the court. With beautiful internal and external living spaces, and spacious bedrooms, this home must be inspected to be truly appreciated.
Main bedroom with walk in robe and en suite.
Well equipped kitchen
Multiple living areas
34 squares (approx) including garage set on 615m2 (approx) block.
Quality features including remote control double garage with internal access, good sized backyard, ducted heating, evaporative cooling, alarm, security system, and lots more!
Located about 22 km from Melbourne's CBD in Sanctuary Lakes with estate security monitoring, this home is a short walk to nearby open space with walking tracks and wetlands, a nd a short drive to the waterfront Village Centre with shopping and dining options, and Sanctuary Lakes Shopping Centre with supermarket and convenience retail. Plus there's optional membership to the golf course and Resort Club with club house, gym, tennis courts and swimming pool.
